description:
Do you like helping customers implement innovative cloud computing solutions and solve technical problems? Would you like to do this using the latest cloud computing technologies? Do you have a knack for helping groups understand application architectures and integration approaches, and the consultative and leadership skills to launch a project on a trajectory to success?


Are you familiar with security best practices for applications, servers, and networks? Do you want to be part of the technical team helping to establish Amazon Web Services (AWS) as a leading technology platform? Would you like to be part of a technical sales group where your opinion is valued as integral part of planning and strategies?
Amazon Web Services is looking for a Solutions Architect to help accelerate our growing Government business as part of the World Wide Public Sector practice. This is an excellent opportunity to join Amazon’s technical teams while also developing your skills and furthering your career within one of the most innovative and progressive technology companies anywhere.


As a Solutions Architect within AWS, you will have the opportunity to help shape and deliver on a strategy to build broad use of Amazon's utility computing web services directly with customers and our ecosystem of system integrators and solution providers. Your broad responsibilities will include: owning the technical engagement and ultimate success around specific implementation projects; defining implementation architectures; developing a deep expertise in the AWS technologies as well as broad know-how around how applications and services are constructed using the AWS platform; and being an technical advisor as it relates to customer applications and services.
As a Solutions Architect on our team, you will provide exceptional technical design and thought leadership to Government business working closely with a world class sales and business development team. You will lead efforts to capture and share best-practice knowledge amongst the AWS solution architect community. You will gain the opportunity to learn from, collaborate with, and educate some of the brightest technical minds in the industry today across the breadth of enterprise architecture.


Roles and Responsibilities:
* Serve as a key member of the account management and business development team in helping to ensure customer success in building and migrating applications, software and services on the AWS platform;
* Engage, Enable and Support systems integrators in their technical implementation efforts in AWS;
* Assist solution providers working with Government Agencies and Institutes to define and implement technical and business strategies that will enable them to sell more of their offerings on the AWS platform;
* Develop and deliver compelling presentations, product demos, sample solutions, and discussions to drive awareness and adoption of Amazon Web Services in Brazilian Government agencies;
* Gain industry recognition and credibility as a regular attendee, panelist and keynote speaker at AWS and third-party technology conferences, trade shows and press events;
* Capture and share best practice knowledge with the worldwide AWS solution architect community;
* Understand the AWS market segments, customer base, and industry verticals in Brazil;

Amazon.com is an Equal Opportunity Employer – Minority / Women / Disability / Veteran / Gender Identity / Sexual Orientation.
